bl.postprocessor
Class FragmentsEnhancer

java.lang.Object
  bl.postprocessor.FragmentsEnhancer
Deprecated. 

public class FragmentsEnhancer
extends java.lang.Object

Reads in a -outputFile of ParSeMiS and enhances it with ClassNumber and EdgeWeights, similar to the ParSeMiS output of M. Huber`s versions. This class is not used anymore, as the writing to a file is omitted.

Author:
Christopher Oßner

FAILING_INDICATOR

private static final java.lang.String FAILING_INDICATOR
Deprecated. 
String that indicates that a graph is from a failing execution. Supposed to be found at the end of a graph-name. Graph-names matching this String will be set to ClassNumber 0.

main

exec

public int exec()
Deprecated. 
For each fragment the corresponding serialized object is looked up to get the annotations for each edge in it`s super-graph. The produced output contains the fragment (nothing changed here) but embeddings got the form: # lg representation of a fragment # name = name of the 1st super-graph this fragment was found in # c = name.endWith("_failing") ? 1 : 0 # a1 = annotations of edge_1 (the first listed in the fragment) in the supergraph #=> NodeIDs fragments file> #=> ClassNumber c #=> EdgeWeights a1 a2 a3 [...] # next embedding ...

Returns:
number of fragments
